# =============================================================================
# SUMMARY OF GAPS IDENTIFIED
# =============================================================================

# 1. Error Propagation: Do child errors bubble up to parent variables?
# 2. Faulted Variable Usage: What happens if you try to use a Faulted variable as input?
# 3. Cached State Syntax: How to enable/configure caching? Cache metadata fields?
# 4. Cache Invalidation: How to mark variables as Dirty? Explicit invalidation syntax?
# 5. Retry Configuration: How to configure retry policies? Is retry automatic or manual?
# 6. Retry Metadata: Is there .retry_count or other retry-related fields?
# 7. Paused State Mechanics: How to pause/resume? Does pipeline block or queue?
# 8. Background Task States: Do [b] background tasks behave differently with states?
# 9. Serial Load States: Are loaded variables in Ready or special "Loaded" state?
# 10. Variable Declaration in Error Blocks: Can we declare variables inside [!] blocks?
# 11. Join State Guarantees: After Join, what states are possible? Only Ready/Faulted?
# 12. Nested State Inheritance: Do nested fields have own states or inherit from parent?
# 13. Primitive Field States: Do pg\string, pg\int primitives have .state?
# 14. Map/Collection States: Can we check state of map values or array elements?
# 15. State as Value: Can we pass .variable.state itself as a value?
# 16. Parallel State Observation: Can we observe Pending state before automatic wait?
# 17. Error Field Structure: Exact structure of .errors array? Error object schema?
# 18. Array/Map Indexing: Syntax for accessing array[0] or map["key"]?
# 19. Constant State Lifecycle: Are constants always Ready? Ever Declared?
# 20. Type Conversion Failures: How do type mismatches affect states?
# 21. Variable Existence vs Faulted: Can we distinguish "doesn't exist" from "Faulted"?
# 22. State Aggregation: Better patterns for checking "all ready" vs "some ready"?
# 23. Queue Control Syntax: What does [Q] actually look like for different operations?
